      "content": "ok that makes sense for the economic side. but can you go deeper into the cultural arguments? like, some people argued that segregation was actually good because it allowed different groups to preserve their own unique traditions and community values without outside interference. i need to find the strongest way to frame that \"cultural preservation\" argument so i can address it in my debate. can you flesh out that specific perspective for me?",
